  SECTION 4 — PROTECTED INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The following elements of the Software are explicitly protected and may NOT
be reproduced, adapted, or used as the basis for any other work without
written permission, even for non-commercial purposes:

  4.1 SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE & SCHEDULING DESIGN
      • FastAPI multi-module backend architecture integrating APScheduler with
        six independent time-zoned jobs (Taiwan close 13:40, US close 05:10,
        morning email 07:00, ETF refresh 18:00, evening data refresh 18:30,
        data health report 19:00), all keyed to Asia/Taipei timezone;
      • Dual-environment override system via REPORT_HOUR/MINUTE,
        ETF_HOLDINGS_HOUR/MINUTE, DATA_REFRESH_HOUR/MINUTE environment
        variables allowing runtime rescheduling without code changes;
      • In-memory cache architecture (_daily_report, _stock_analyses,
        _etf_holdings dicts) with SHA256 header token authentication
        separating read-only public endpoints from write endpoints
        (API_SECRET_REPORT / API_SECRET_STOCK dual-secret model);
      • Multi-tier data persistence design: in-memory cache → per-symbol
        JSON snapshots → prev/curr ETF snapshot pairs for change detection.

  4.2 ACTIVE ETF (主動式ETF) DATA PIPELINE
      • The curated ACTIVE_ETFS registry mapping 34 Taiwan active ETFs
        to their fund names, using "A" suffix (stock-type, codes 00980A–
        00999A, 00400A–00403A) and "D" suffix (bond-type, 00980D–00986D)
        classification conventions as implemented in etf_holdings.py;
      • The fetch_etf_holdings() scraping engine targeting MoneyDJ
        (https://www.moneydj.com/KMDJ/Wiki/...) with pd.read_html() table
        detection, 4-hour TTL cache, and automatic fallback to etfinfo.tw;
      • The _repair_mojibake() character encoding recovery algorithm that
        corrects Latin-1/UTF-8 conversion errors in MoneyDJ responses
        (e.g., "å°ç©é»" → "台積電");
      • The compute_holdings_changes() snapshot comparison algorithm that
        identifies new_positions, exited_positions, increased_weight, and
        decreased_weight between prev and current ETF holdings snapshots;
      • The fetch_etf_sector_summary() aggregation pipeline mapping Taiwan
        industry codes (01–38) to named sectors ("半導體", "金融",
        "AI與雲端", etc.), with multi-horizon baseline tracking against
        historical snapshots at 1d/7d/30d/91d/182d/273d/365d intervals;
      • The build_etf_email_section() HTML renderer generating per-ETF
        top-5 holdings tables with share-change badges.

  4.3 INDIVIDUAL STOCK ANALYSIS MATHEMATICAL MODELS
      • The analyze_stock() weighted composite scoring engine in
        analysis.py computing 60+ technical signals mapped to a continuous
        score in [-2.0, +2.0] with five rating tiers:
        strong_buy (≥2.5) / buy (≥1.0) / hold (≥-1.0) /
        sell (≥-2.5) / strong_sell (<-2.5);
      • Moving average signal weights: MA Golden Cross (MA5>MA20) ±2.0,
        short-term trend (MA5 vs MA10) ±1.0, mid-term trend
        (MA20 vs MA60) ±1.0, quarterly line (price vs MA60) ±0.5,
        annual line (price vs MA240) ±0.5;
      • The Taiwan-specific Slow Stochastic KD formula:
        K = (2/3)×prev_K + (1/3)×RSV;  D = (2/3)×prev_D + (1/3)×K,
        with KD Golden/Dead Cross signals ±2.0, overbought/oversold
        thresholds at 80/20, as implemented in indicators.py;
      • RSI divergence detection over a 5-bar sliding window:
        price-up/RSI-down scores -1.5 (bearish divergence),
        price-down/RSI-up scores +1.5 (bullish divergence);
      • OBV (On-Balance Volume) divergence detection over a 10-bar window:
        price-up/OBV-down = -1.5 (volume weakness),
        price-down/OBV-up = +1.5 (volume accumulation);
      • Volume ratio analysis: current volume vs 20-day MA volume;
        ratio >2.0 on up-day = +1.5 (explosive bullish),
        ratio >2.0 on down-day = -1.5 (capitulation sell signal);
      • The _linear_regression_forecast() function fitting
        Price = slope×day + intercept over last 20/60 bars,
        returning predicted price, pred_change_pct, 95% confidence
        interval [lower, upper], R² goodness-of-fit, and slope_per_day;
      • The _analyze_institutional_investors() dual-market scoring model:
        Taiwan 三大法人 (Foreign ±0.5, Trust ±0.3, Dealer ±0.2,
        Total ±1.0) plus 3-day sustained trend bonus ±1.0;
        US insider ownership >20% = +0.5, institutional >70% = +1.0;
      • Herfindahl-Hirschman Index (HHI = Σ percentage²) concentration
        classification: >2500 "高度集中", 1500–2500 "中度集中",
        <1500 "分散", as implemented in chip_analysis.py.

  4.4 DATA ACQUISITION & MULTI-SOURCE ARBITRAGE
      • Priority-ordered multi-source fallback chain for Taiwan quotes:
        bulk TWSE/TPEX cache (5-min TTL) → TWSE MIS API
        (mis.twse.com.tw) → Sina Finance → Tencent Finance → yfinance;
      • The get_investors_data() dual-path logic: FinMind API for Taiwan
        三大法人 + 融資融券 data; SEC filing parsing for US institutional
        holdings — unified into a single normalized response schema;
      • Multi-interval OHLCV caching: 24h TTL for daily, 7d for weekly
        data, with df_to_ohlcv_list() standardizing output to
        [{time, open, high, low, close, volume}] JSON format.

  4.5 WATCHLIST DATA STRUCTURE & TAXONOMY
      • The nested watchlist hierarchy (地區 > 產業 > 細分類 > 四級分類)
        with 70+ Taiwan subcategories spanning 半導體, 電子, 金融,
        鋼鐵, 航運, 生技醫療, etc., as defined in watchlist.py;
      • The leaf node schema {symbol, name, name_en, tags[]} enabling
        multilingual display and multi-tag sector filtering;
      • The generate_daily_report() aggregation logic that de-duplicates
        symbols across nested watchlist categories, computes per-sector
        average scores, and ranks top_opportunities and top_risks.

